REST - Representational State Transfer
   its a style of designing webservices where client communicate with server via http methods.
GET   - Fetches data
POST  - Create new data
PUT   - update Full resource.
PATCH  - Partial Update
DELETE - Reomves data.

JSON - Javascript Object Notation..
  It is lightweight text format used to store and exchange data between systems.

EX: {
    "name":"hari",
    "age": 30,
    "salary": 5000
}
Rules: 
  1. Data is in key value pair.
  2. Key must be in double Quotes
  3. Values can be of String, number, boolean, array, object, null.
     {
        "name":"hari", // sring
        "age": 30, // number
        "salary": 5000, //number
        "deptId": null, //null
        "isActive": true // boolean
     }
     //Array Representation
     {
        "fruits": ["Apple", "grapes", "Oranges"]  //array representation
     }

     //Object representation   
     {
        "empId": 101,
        "empName": "Hari",
        empDept: {
           "dName": "ECE",
           "dDesc": "Electronics" 
        }
     }

@Controller - 
   - Used to create a Web controller
   - It is Class level annotation      
   - If class is annotated with controller and mapping the urls then it is ready to pick the requests from client and process it and send out the response back to client. 
    It can return  HTML page / Thymeleaf pages(it has the capability to use java object and paint it in the HTML page)
@RestController 
  - Used to create REST API
  - Returns the JSON string directly.
@RequestMapping:
    - maps URL requests to a class or method. 
    - It is class level/Method level annotation.
@Pathvariable:
    - Used to read value from URL path
    - Argument level variable
    @requestMapping("/users/data/{id}")
@RequestParam:
     Used to read query parameter from URL.
     ex: /users/data?id=120&sal=5000
@RequestBody:
    Read JSON data sent by client in http request and convert it to java object. 
